MODULE-1:- GOVERNANCE
============================================================================================================================================
Governance:- Governance is the process of definig rules, policies,responsibility and controls
            to ensure system operate safely,legally and effectively.

Governance = Rules + Monitering +Accountability

Benefits:-
-> System follow company policies.
-> Laws and regulations are obyed.
-> Risks are controlled. 
-> People are accountable.

Why Governance is important:-
-> Ensures compliance with laws and regulations
-> Reduce risks
-> Improves accountability
-> Protects company assests
-> Maintains customer trust.


Components of Governance:-
->Policies:-Policies define organizational rules.
->Standards:-Standard define specific requirement.
->Procedures:- step-by-step guidelines.
->Controls:- Mechanisms used to enforce policies.

Government in software development:-
Types of IT Governance:-
-> Data Governance:- Management od data quality, security, and availability.
->Security Governance:- Defines security responsibilities and controls.
-> AI Governance:- Ensures AI system are fair,transparent,traceable.

Important Governance Frameworks:
-> COBIT- Control Objectives for Information and related technologies.
Used for:-
-> IT governance
-> Risk management

-> ISO 27001:- International standard for information Security Management.
Used for:
-> Security Controls
-> Risk management

