MODULE-5 PRIVACY
====================================================================================================================================================

Privacy:- Privacy is the right of individuals to control how their personal information
          is collected, used, stored and shared.

Personal data Examples:-
-> Name
-> Email
-> Phone number
-> Address

Privacy Principles
1.) Data Minimization:-Collect only neccessary.
Bad Example:
Asking date of birth when not required.
Good Example:
Collecting only email for newsletter subscription.

2.) Purpose Limitation:-Use data only for the purpose specified.
Example:
Email collected for login cannot be used for marketing without consent.

3.)Consent:-Users must agree before data collection.
Example:- Cookie consent banners.\

4.) Transparency:-
Organisations must clearly explain:
->What data is collected.
->Why it is collected.
->How it will be used.

5.) Data Retention:-
Keep data only as long as necessary.
Example: Delete inactive user records after a defined period.


