Module-3:Ethical AI
=========================================================================================
Ethical AI:-
Ethical AI refers to designing,devolping and deploying AI System 
resposible so they respect human rights and societal values.

Why Ehical Ai required:-


Core Principle of Ethical AI:
1.) Failrness:- Ai should treat all people equally.
   eg: Suppose an AI Hiring system favours men over women because 
       historial hiring data was biased.
2.) Transparency:- Users should understand how Ai makes decisions.
  eg:-Banks expalins why a loan application is rejected.
3.) Accountability:- Someone must be responsible for AI decisions.
 eg:-A company must investigate harmful AI outcomes.
4.) Reliability and safety:- AI should work consistently and safely.
 eg:-Self-driving cars must be throughly tested.
5.)Privacy and Security:-AI must protect user data.
 eg:- chatbots should not expose confidential chats.
6.)Human Oversight:- Human should remain invloved in important decisions.
eg:- Doctors review AI-generated diagnoses before treatment.


AI Bias:-Bias occurs when AI produces unfair outcomes.

Causes
Biased Data
Example:- An AI model trained mostly on one demographic group.

Biased Design
Example:- Developers fair to consider diverse user groups.


